wikipedia_page.main: George Wenman (born 27 October 1805 at Benenden, Kent; died 19 January 1837 at Brookland, Kent) was an English professional cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1825 to 1834.  He was mainly associated with Kent and made 9 known appearances in first-class matches.

response: |Nine first-class appearances, five of them for Kent. Brother of George Wenman and cousin of Ned Wenman.
